---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "About";
---

<Layout>
  <h1>About Me</h1>
  <section id="text">
    <div class="text-wrapper">
      <p>
        I’m interested in marketing and digital strategy, with a background in
        UX and human-computer interaction. My work focuses on understanding how
        people discover, engage with, and respond to digital experiences across
        platforms.
      </p>
      <p>
        By combining UX research with content strategy and storytelling, I enjoy
        translating audience insights into clear messaging, engaging content,
        and meaningful brand experiences.
      </p>
      <p>
        Alongside my UX projects, I create digital content through the Starbucks
        Green Apron Creator program. This experience has given me direct insight
        into audience engagement, digital storytelling, and how brands can
        connect authentically with online communities.
      </p>
      <p>
        Being part of the original pilot group of creators allowed me to
        collaborate on content strategy and participate in a month-long training
        and mentorship program focused on responsible content creation, brand
        storytelling, and digital communication.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="spacer"></div>
</Layout>
<style>
  h1 {
    font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  #text {
    max-width: 800px;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.5rem;
  }

  section {
    min-height: 65vh;
  }

  .text-wrapper {
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin: auto;
    outline: 2px solid var(--dark-text);
    background-color: var(--background-color-light);
  }
</style>
